    "body": "Some servers limit how many times you can log in within a time period, eg once every minute. \r\nIf you log in once, and then log in again with a vanilla client before that time has passed, it catches a connection throttled error.\r\nIf you log in once, and then log in again with mineflayer it shows nothing. It doesn't crash, it doesn't give an error. it just sits there.\r\n\r\nMineflayer should throw an error when it gets a connection throttled, or even return an error automatically after n seconds (\"logging in timed out!\")",
